        <h2 id="uno">Recipe #1 - Teriyaki Chicken</h2>
        
        <img src = "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/-teriyaki-chicken.jpg/2560px--teriyaki-chicken.jpg" width = "500">
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 30 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 8 servings</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table class = "recipe">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Skinless & Boneless Chicken Thighs</td>
                    <td>8 thighs</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Soy Sauce</td>
                    <td>1 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sugar</td>
                    <td>1 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Pressed Garlic Cloves</td>
                    <td>6 cloves</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Grated Ginger</td>
                    <td>2 tablespoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Black Pepper</td>
                    <td>1/4 teaspoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Cornstarch</td>
                    <td>2 tablespoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Pineapple Juice</td>
                    <td>1 tablespoon</td>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Combine ingredients excluding cornstarch and chicken. High heat for 3 minutes.<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Coat chicken in soy sauce, leave refrigerated for at least an hour.<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Combine cornstarch and water, stir until thickened.<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> Brush sauce on chicken and grill.
        <br>
        <strong>Step 5:</strong> Slice chicken into strips, and serve. Enjoy!
</p>
        <h2 id="dos">Recipe #2 - Eggrolls</h2>
        
        <img src = "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/95/Lumpiang_Shanghai_%28Philippines%29.jpg" width = "500">
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 1 hr 45 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 40 egg rolls</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table class = "recipe">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Ground Pork</td>
                    <td>1 1/2 lb</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Minced Shrimp</td>
                    <td>1/2 lb</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Cellophane Noodles</td>
                    <td>8 oz</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Eggs</td>
                    <td>2 eggs</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Fish Sauce</td>
                    <td>5 tablespoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Minced Onion</td>
                    <td>1 onion</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Pepper</td>
                    <td>1 tablespoon</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Egg Roll Wrappers</td>
                    <td>2 packages</td>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Combine ground pork, noodles, onions, egg yolks, pepper, fish sauce.<br>
        
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Cook.<br>
        
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Roll. Serve.
</p>
        <h2 id="tres">Recipe #3 - General Tso's Chicken</h2>
        
        <img src = "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/General_Tso%27s_Chicken.JPG" width = "500">
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 25 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 4 people</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table class = "recipe">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Chicken Thigh</td>
                    <td>1.4 lb</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Orange Sauce</td>
                    <td>1 cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Brocoli</td>
                    <td>10s</td>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Brush chicken with orange sauce. Cook chicken.
<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Plate it and add broccoli. Enjoy!
</p>
        
